node.title: Children fall 10 metres from jumping castle blown into air at Tasmanian school
node.alt: A COVID-19 information sign with the Sydney Opera House pictured in the background.
node.description: Several children have fallenÂ from a height of 10 metres, causing serious injuries, after wind blew a jumping castle into the air at a primary school in Tasmania's north-west.
node.content: ["Several children have fallen\u00a0from a height of 10 metres, causing serious injuries, after wind blew a jumping castle into the air at a primary school in Tasmania's north-west.", "Ambulance Tasmania said it was responding to a \"major incident\" and multiple ambulance vehicles\u00a0were heading to the scene at Hillcrest Primary School.", "\"A\u00a0wind event caused a jumping castle to lift into the air,\" Tasmanian police said in a statement.", "\"Several children fell from a height of about 10 metres around 10am and are currently receiving medical treatment at the scene.", "\"Some serious injuries have occurred.\"", "People are being asked\u00a0to avoid the area.", "A notice has been sent out to parents of children at the school.", "More to come."]
